data.description: **Astoria Heights**This truly unique and oversized 3 Br/2.5 bath residence was completely gut renovated, and even extended over an eighteen month period. The master craftsmanship used is evident even before entering the home. The entire front facade was replaced using a lighter colored brick, bluestone window sills and stairs, triple pane casement windows, and a copper door. As you enter the home, the expansive open concept floorplan is evident. There is a living room with a fireplace, a dining room and library, a half bathroom, and a state of the art European kitchen. Perfect for the avid cook and even better for entertaining; there is a center island, granite counter tops, Miele appliances, and imported Italian cabinetry. Sliding glass doors lead you a covered porch and a gorgeous paved yard. The second floor features three huge bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms. The master bedroom with an en-suite bath has a stand-up shower and a tub. Best of all, it has its own private terrace and a skylight with. The full basement which has an outside entrance from the front of the home has high ceilings, tons of storage, a washer and dryer, half-bath, and porcelain tiles throughout. Traditional homes in the immediate area measure 34' in depth; this home was extended to 47' on all floors. Throughout the home you will find white oak flooring, central AC, recessed lighting, custom doors and millwork, and much more. There are three outdoor areas, parking for two cars, with easy access to transportation, shopping, and the city. This home is truly a rare find especially with when taking into consideration of the unparalleled craftsmanship invested.
data.whatILove: The exquisite renovation, large rooms, three private outdoor spaces, and original Versace details abound
